   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, Southgate Cregmile in Stevenson, Ala. to Crittenden Cregmile, 1863, September 5</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>1863 September 5 Southgate Cregmile in Stevenson, Ala., to his brother Crittenden. Assures him that he and all their hometown boys are well. Has arrived in Ala. before the rest of the division which has just been ordered up. Gen. Negley has left word for Col. Wilder to make sure eight days of rations are packed in wagons and two days in haversacks, before leaving Cowan. The 2nd Division is near Chattanooga, but the rest of the Army of the Cumberland is in Atlanta, where they must fight or be ravaged. Chattanooga, normally a very busy railroad town, has been brought to a halt with Col. Wilder's passing through. Urges him to write soon.</abstract>
